text:
Great question, very personal to me!

I strongly believe that a company is no longer a ‘Startup’ when it no longer plays to win.

This is from my direct experience - most “larger” companies (including highly funded startups), only play not to loose. Here are some symptoms -

• People pass the buck right, left, and center
• Most meetings and agenda end with someone saying will get back to you on that (most times they just don’t)
• Support has no clue about how product works and only care about avg. ticket closures (that what they also get measured by)
• Mediocrity is rampant and glares at you everyone who can see. But is never acknowledged.
• Processes are a blockers. (this one is still okay to live with). 
• Things get measured only to make a report (I have seen worst)
• And more…
